summary:
I have found the needle and fixed the bug. The `hashCode` method in `src/Product.java` was using `category` instead of `sku` to generate the hash code, which caused massive collisions since there were many products across very few categories. 

I modified `hashCode` to use `sku.hashCode()`:
```java
    @Override
    public int hashCode() {
        return sku.hashCode();
    }
```
After recompiling the source files, `test.sh` has verified that the max chain length is back to healthy levels and all tests passed.
